29 Dec 2012 08:40






Why guard/film/stare at a black box all the time if the object within only affects anyone that sees it? Nothing is mentioned that necessitates additional containment procedures beyond locking it in a box and making sure no one opens said box. Which would also make this Safe, not Euclid. Moreover, a containment breach in its glorious entirety would be one person, sitting in front of a (formerly) locked box, staring at the object naked and hairless. Until he or she dies of thirst. Or sepsis. So not only is it containable, it is easily re containable.

I like the rest of the article, beyond the containment procedures, because it's a simple and neat concept that is well executed. Null vote, until it's either edited or someone convinces me that I'm being unreasonable.







